---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Simulation Test Room | EES"
  description="Our purpose-built TestCell for real-world hydronic ceiling panel testing — designed and constructed in-house to ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 standards."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Simulation Test Room</h1>
      <p>Purpose-built to prove our hydronic ceiling systems under real-world conditions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Facility Overview -->
  <section class="facility-hero">
    <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/308748357_831370331371037_4396639554076040798_n.webp" alt="EES simulation test room facility with hydronic system equipment and test cell structure" loading="eager" />
    <div class="facility-overlay">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="facility-label">Our Facility</p>
        <h2>The EES TestCell</h2>
        <p class="facility-desc">A full-scale, instrumented room built inside our Geelong workshop — designed to test hydronic ceiling panels under controlled, repeatable conditions aligned to ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 standards.</p>
        <div class="facility-specs">
          <div class="spec">
            <span class="spec-value">3.6 × 4.8m</span>
            <span class="spec-label">Floor Area</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec">
            <span class="spec-value">3.0m</span>
            <span class="spec-label">Ceiling Height</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec">
            <span class="spec-value">7.5m²</span>
            <span class="spec-label">North-Facing Glass</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec">
            <span class="spec-value">R2.0</span>
            <span class="spec-label">Wall Insulation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Video Section — Facility -->
  <section class="section video-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="video-layout">
        <div class="video-wrapper">
          <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="auto" poster="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/639607_7582f9e8760f4b8c8deb96294d92f1c3_mv2_crop.webp">
            <source src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_FInal/video.MP4" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
        <div class="video-text">
          <p class="video-label">Inside the TestCell</p>
          <h2>A Real Room Built for Real Testing</h2>
          <p>What you're looking at is the interior of our purpose-built simulation room — a fully enclosed, instrumented space constructed inside our Geelong workshop to Australian Standard specifications.</p>
          <p>The room features R2.0 insulated walls, a 7.5m² commercial-grade double-glazed window on the north face, and a suspended ceiling grid fitted with our hydronic panels. It's not a sealed lab — it's designed to behave like a real occupied space, with solar gain, ventilation and thermal mass.</p>
          <p>Every surface is monitored. Thermal imaging cameras, ASHRAE-55 comfort carts, heat flux meters and air temperature stratification strings capture continuous data throughout each test cycle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hydronic Panels in Action -->
  <section class="section panels-action">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Test Footage</p>
        <h2>Hydronic Ceiling Panels <span class="h2-light">in Action</span></h2>
        <p class="section-desc">No fans, no ducts, no moving air — just radiant energy delivered silently through the ceiling.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="action-grid">
        <div class="action-card">
          <div class="action-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <path d="M20 8v4M20 28v4M8 20h4M28 20h4M12.3 12.3l2.8 2.8M24.9 24.9l2.8 2.8M12.3 27.7l2.8-2.8M24.9 15.1l2.8-2.8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Radiant Transfer</h3>
          <p>The panels exchange energy with the room through radiation — the most effective mechanism for thermal comfort. Surfaces warm or cool evenly without disturbing the air.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="action-card">
          <div class="action-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M10 30V18l10-8 10 8v12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M16 30v-8h8v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M14 22h12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="2 2"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Silent Operation</h3>
          <p>No compressors, no ductwork, no fans in the conditioned space. The system circulates water through capillary tubes — the only sound is comfortable silence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="action-card">
          <div class="action-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="10" y="10" width="20" height="20" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <path d="M10 20h20M20 10v20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="15" cy="15" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
              <circle cx="25" cy="15" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
              <circle cx="15" cy="25" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
              <circle cx="25" cy="25" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Rapid Response</h3>
          <p>Capillary tube mats have minimal thermal mass — the system reaches target temperature quickly and adjusts in real time to changing loads and conditions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Finished Room -->
  <section class="section finished-room">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">The Completed Room</p>
        <h2>Multiple Ceiling Surfaces, <span class="h2-light">One System</span></h2>
        <p class="section-desc">The TestCell ceiling is divided into bays, each fitted with a different architectural finish — all powered by the same hydronic capillary tube system beneath.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ceiling-showcase">
        <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/ceiling-panels-labeled.webp" alt="TestCell ceiling showing five different finishing surfaces — adhesive vinyl coated wallpaper, rendered coating, perforated metal panel, mini-orb, and plasterboard with vinyl finish" />
      </div>

      <div class="panel-grid">
        <div class="panel-card">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/639607_dee5110879914401aa781f84eeb92cdc_mv2.webp" alt="3D render of hydronic ceiling panel showing capillary tube mat and insulation layers" />
          <div class="panel-card-text">
            <h3>Panel Design</h3>
            <p>Each tile combines insulation, a capillary tube mat and an architectural finish into a single modular unit that drops into standard 600 × 1200mm ceiling grids.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-card">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/IMG_0030.webp" alt="Underside of hydronic ceiling panel showing blue capillary tube mat bonded to insulation" />
          <div class="panel-card-text">
            <h3>Capillary Tube Mat</h3>
            <p>Blue polypropylene capillary tubes bonded to the insulation layer. The tight tube spacing ensures uniform heat distribution across the entire panel surface.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-card">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/IMG_0041.webp" alt="Finished perforated metal panel face — clean, architectural appearance" />
          <div class="panel-card-text">
            <h3>Finished Surface</h3>
            <p>The room-facing side accepts a range of finishes — perforated metal, plasterboard, rendered coating, mini-orb, or vinyl. The system is invisible to occupants.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Thermal Performance -->
  <div class="thermal-group">
    <div class="diagonal-divider" style="background: #fff;">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1440 120" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <polygon points="0,0 0,120 1440,120" fill="#0E2B47" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <section class="thermal-results">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header section-header--light">
          <p class="section-label section-label--light">Thermal Imaging</p>
          <h2>Measured Performance</h2>
          <p class="section-desc section-desc--light">Thermal imaging confirms uniform surface temperature distribution across the ceiling panels — in both heating and cooling modes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="thermal-comparison">
          <div class="thermal-card">
            <div class="thermal-img-wrap">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/thermal-heating-full.webp" alt="Thermal image of ceiling panels in heating mode — uniform warm surface temperatures shown in red and orange" />
            </div>
            <div class="thermal-info">
              <span class="thermal-mode thermal-mode--heat">Heating Mode</span>
              <p>Ceiling panels at 27.6°C. Even red/orange distribution confirms uniform heat delivery with no cold spots or thermal bridging at panel joints.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="thermal-card">
            <div class="thermal-img-wrap">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/thermal-cooling-full.webp" alt="Thermal image of ceiling panels in cooling mode — uniform cool surface temperatures shown in blue and green" />
            </div>
            <div class="thermal-info">
              <span class="thermal-mode thermal-mode--cool">Cooling Mode</span>
              <p>Ceiling panels at 14.4°C. Blue thermal signature shows effective cooling across all panel surfaces — no warm spots or condensation risk.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="thermal-equipment">
          <div class="equipment-item">
            <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/IMG_7953.webp" alt="Avio thermal imaging camera on Manfrotto tripod used for ceiling surface temperature measurement" />
            <span>Thermal Imaging Camera</span>
          </div>
          <div class="equipment-item">
            <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/278089988_1024252955112112_2213671243500220494_n.webp" alt="ASHRAE-55 thermal comfort cart with sensors for air temperature stratification and operative temperature measurement" />
            <span>ASHRAE-55 Comfort Cart</span>
          </div>
          <div class="equipment-item">
            <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/sensor-.webp" alt="Environmental sensor array used for monitoring air temperature, humidity and velocity in the test room" />
            <span>Environmental Sensors</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="diagonal-divider" style="background: #0E2B47;">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1440 120" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <polygon points="0,0 0,120 1440,120" fill="#f8f9fa" />
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- System Design -->
  <section class="section system-design">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">System Architecture</p>
        <h2>How It <span class="h2-light">All Connects</span></h2>
        <p class="section-desc">The hydronic system uses low-voltage pumps, mixing valves and a heat pump to circulate temperature-controlled water through the ceiling panels.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="system-grid">
        <div class="system-card system-card--wide">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/test-hydronic-2-230616.webp" alt="3D isometric view of the complete hydronic ceiling system showing ceiling panels, piping runs, mixing station and equipment cabinet" />
          <div class="system-card-text">
            <h3>Complete System Overview</h3>
            <p>Hot and cold water loops feed through a mixing station into the ceiling grid. Each panel connects independently, allowing zone-by-zone control across the room.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="system-card">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/diagram.webp" alt="System schematic showing heat pump, water tank, pressure tank, vacuum relief valve, water pump and capillary tube mat connections" />
          <div class="system-card-text">
            <h3>System Schematic</h3>
            <p>Heat pump drives water through the heat exchanger and into the capillary tube mats via the circulation pump. Pressure tanks and vacuum relief valves ensure stable, safe operation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="system-card">
          <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/plumbing-2.webp" alt="Detailed plumbing schematic showing water tank, valves, pump and capillary tube mat connections" />
          <div class="system-card-text">
            <h3>Plumbing Detail</h3>
            <p>Modular PPR piping with brass fittings, 24V DC circulation pumps and switching actuators. Each component is low-voltage for safety and efficiency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Development Story -->
  <section class="section dev-story">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">The Build</p>
        <h2>How We Built <span class="h2-light">the TestCell</span></h2>
        <p class="section-desc">From steel framing to a fully instrumented simulation room — every element was designed and constructed in-house at our Geelong facility.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">1</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/db40c3a0-63a3-484b-ae40-10b1c7887877.webp" alt="Steel stud framing of the test room structure inside the EES workshop" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Steel Frame Construction</h3>
            <p>The room structure was built from steel studs to Australian Standard specifications — a real room with proper wall framing, not a temporary enclosure.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">2</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images timeline-images--double">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Final_webp/278aed21-6bc8-479a-863c-9ad2c72bb524.webp" alt="Aerial view of the test room wrapped in building membrane during construction" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG-4183.webp" alt="Double-glazed north-facing window installed in the test room wall" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Insulation &amp; Glazing</h3>
            <p>R2.0 batt insulation throughout, building wrap membrane, and a 7.5m² commercial-grade double-glazed window on the north face — designed to simulate worst-case solar gain conditions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">3</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images timeline-images--triple">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG_7483.webp" alt="Blue capillary tube mat laid out on insulation panel before assembly" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG_0046.webp" alt="Completed ceiling panel showing capillary tubes bonded to foil-faced insulation" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG_0048.webp" alt="Ceiling panel standing in the workshop showing tube mat and insulation layers" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Panel Manufacturing</h3>
            <p>Capillary tube mats were bonded to insulation panels and fitted with architectural finishes. Each panel was built and pressure-tested in-house before installation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">4</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images timeline-images--double">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/191330305_1530368173988011_309953162325682046_n.webp" alt="Close-up of blue capillary tube mat being installed on a ceiling panel" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/Mats.webp" alt="Capillary tube mats prepared and ready for bonding to ceiling panels" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Capillary Tube Installation</h3>
            <p>Polypropylene capillary tubes installed at tight spacing to ensure uniform heat distribution. The mats are lightweight, flexible and deliver rapid thermal response times.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">5</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images timeline-images--triple">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/plumbing-full.webp" alt="Assembled hydronic plumbing manifold with pumps, valves and pressure tanks" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG_6357.webp" alt="Hydronic manifold with flow meters and individual circuit valves" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/1.webp" alt="Ceiling panels plumbed and connected on the workbench before installation" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Plumbing &amp; Hydraulics</h3>
            <p>PPR piping with brass fittings connects each panel to the central manifold. Flow meters on each circuit allow individual panel monitoring and balancing. The system uses 24V DC pumps and actuators.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">6</span>
            <div class="timeline-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images timeline-images--double">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/260922725_615362759662446_7108777509642017868_n.webp" alt="Early prototype water tank with pressure gauge, copper piping and expansion vessel" loading="lazy" />
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/IMG_6445.webp" alt="Water tank plumbing connections and expansion vessel during system assembly" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Water Storage &amp; Heat Exchange</h3>
            <p>Hot and cold water tanks with heat exchangers, expansion vessels and pressure gauges. The system can switch between heating and cooling modes via 24V DC actuated valves.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">
            <span class="timeline-number">7</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <div class="timeline-images">
              <img src="/image/WIP/TestRoom_Development_webp/269722110_2110682989094831_8008561485059951530_n.webp" alt="Worker installing underfloor heating mats inside the test room during final fit-out" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <h3>Final Fit-Out &amp; Commissioning</h3>
            <p>Ceiling panels installed, underfloor heating mats laid, instrumentation positioned and the full system commissioned. The TestCell was ready for its first controlled test run.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-box">
        <h2>Interested in our research?</h2>
        <p>We offer third-party testing in our facility and are happy to discuss our hydronic ceiling panel technology with architects, engineers and building professionals.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Facility Hero */
  .facility-hero {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 520px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .facility-hero > img {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .facility-overlay {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    min-height: 520px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    padding: 3rem 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to top,
      rgba(14, 43, 71, 0.92) 0%,
      rgba(14, 43, 71, 0.7) 40%,
      rgba(14, 43, 71, 0.3) 70%,
      transparent 100%
    );
  }

  .facility-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .facility-overlay h2 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .facility-desc {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .facility-specs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .spec {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
  }

  .spec-value {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #fff;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .spec-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .facility-hero,
    .facility-overlay {
      min-height: 420px;
    }

    .facility-overlay h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .facility-specs {
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .spec {
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    }

    .spec-value {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
  }

  /* Video Section */
  .video-section {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .video-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .video-wrapper {
    border-radius: 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    height: 100%;
  }

  .video-wrapper video {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .video-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #2061B7;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .video-text h2 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .video-text p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .video-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .video-text h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }

  /* Section Headers (reusable) */
  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #2061B7;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .h2-light {
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .section-desc {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #666;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .section-header--light h2 {
    color: #fff;
  }

  .section-label--light {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
  }

  .section-desc--light {
